Text.Value: I don't know. But I'm hungry.
Free from this nightmare? It doesn't feel possible...
Leave.
You can't. It's not possible.
Just tell me where to find him. I'll do the rest.
But even if you can kill him - what then? What happens to us?
How do I open your cell? Does he have the key?
I've been hungry for so, so long...
Please, help us.
The last thing I remember, I was drinking with a pale, beautiful elf. We laughed, we kissed, we stumbled back to this palace, and then...
*Under the grime, you can see how pale he is. You can see the hunger in his eyes - in all of their eyes. Each one is an emaciated, starving vampire spawn.*
You can't stop him. No one can stop him.
Please, you shouldn't be here. He'll find you. And he won't kill you.
Please, go. Do whatever you have to.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: OM happened, Astarion escaped the grapple without attacking the prisoner.

Text.Value: Please, help us. We just want to be free.
Busy, that's what I am.
Please... what are you?
His staff - it controls everything down here.
He carved it himself - said it bound me to his ascension.
How did this happen to you?
*More than that, you can see that each prisoner is marked with a scar - the same as one of the runes from Astarion's back.*
He never fed us. All we've ever known is hunger.
I'll set you free - what else?
He won't ever let you die.
Whatever you do, just do it quickly. I can't go on like this...
Then it gets so dark. I woke up here. Like this.
He called me so many sweet things. My name sounded like music on his tongue.
Where are the keys to your cells?
You haven't seen his rage. You don't know what he can do.
His staff - it controls everything down here.
I'm going to help you. I'm going to kill Cazador.
I - I don't know. It's all I've ever felt...
I don't know. I just don't want to die down here. Please...
No - no, you can't leave us here. Not now - not like this!
I have no intention of freeing a bunch of ravenous spawn.
Don't leave us. You can't leave us!
Please hurry. Please, save us.
The grand chamber, just ahead...
The elf that brought you here - what was his name?
*Hollow-eyed faces stare out of the cells. Some meet your eyes, but most look away. There's an almost physical stink of decay and neglect.*
Please, no more. I can't take any more.
Sit tight - I'll be back.
That scar on your face - what does it mean?
Sebastian. I'm - I was - I'm not sure. It was all so long ago.
How long has it been since you fed?
Damn you. Damn you...

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: OM happened, prisoner pissed at Astarion
EditorData.NodeContext: Small voice, lost in his own head, still cursing Astarion

Text.Value: I don't know what that means. I don't know what any of this means...
*More than that, you can see that each prisoner is marked with a scar - a rune carved into their flesh.*
I'll try. I promise I'll try.
What do you want to happen?
What am I? What are you?!
Astarion. I'll never forget him.
And then? What happens to us?
He'll find you, you know. And he won't kill you.
But he never sets it down - you'll never get it.
That depends on you. Can you control your hunger?
I just want to breathe free air one last time...
I'm a friend. Who are you?
I'll find a way.

Synopsis:
Dialog with a group of prisoners in Cazador's Palace when Astarion is not in the party.
Also triggered when Astarion is in the party and you already had an Origin Moment with him at this place.
